<p>&nbsp;Transplanting a large number of grafts is a detailed and time-intensive process. In cases of advanced hair loss, surgeons must carefully extract and implant follicles to avoid damaging the donor area. A 5000 graft procedure may take over eight hours to complete, with costs in Turkey averaging between $1,900 and $2,750. The same procedure could cost significantly more abroad, such as around £8,500 in the UK. Pricing also varies depending on the method used, including FUE, Sapphire FUE, DHI, stem cell-supported transplants, or robotic techniques, each offering different benefits and cost ranges.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Hair transplantation itself is a well-established medical solution for hair loss, made possible through advancements in technology. The procedure involves transferring hair follicles from a donor area, typically the nape of the neck where hair is resistant to shedding, to areas experiencing hair loss. Because the patient’s own follicles are used, there is no risk of rejection. This method is considered both natural and permanent, and it has become a reliable solution for individuals dealing with thinning or baldness.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Not everyone is automatically suitable for a hair transplant. Before proceeding, specialists conduct medical tests to evaluate the patient’s condition, including the quality and availability of donor hair. If the donor area is insufficient relative to the bald area, multiple sessions may be required or the procedure may not be recommended. While most adults can undergo the treatment, it is generally not suitable for very young or very elderly individuals, and alternative treatments may be suggested in such cases.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Preparation before the procedure plays a crucial role in ensuring successful results. Patients are advised to avoid alcohol, smoking, caffeine, and certain vitamins prior to the operation, as these can affect blood flow and healing. Hair should be clean, and comfortable clothing is recommended to prevent damage to newly implanted follicles. Medical conditions or medications must be disclosed to the doctor beforehand. Proper preparation helps minimize risks and ensures the procedure can proceed smoothly.</p>
<p>&nbsp;During the transplantation process, multiple specialists often work simultaneously to maximize efficiency. Hair follicles are carefully extracted from the donor area and prepared as grafts, each containing one to three hairs. Small incisions are then made in the recipient area, ensuring proper depth, angle, and direction for a natural appearance. The grafts are implanted one by one into these channels. This meticulous process is key to achieving both aesthetic and long-lasting results.</p>
<p>&nbsp;After the procedure, careful post-operative care is essential for proper healing and optimal outcomes. Patients must avoid touching or washing the hair for the first few days and should sleep on their back using a soft pillow to protect the grafts. Tight clothing, excessive sweating, and exposure to sunlight should be avoided. Medications prescribed by the doctor must be taken as directed. Following these instructions closely significantly improves the success rate and speed of recovery.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The results of a hair transplant depend on multiple factors, including graft quality, patient health, lifestyle habits, and adherence to aftercare instructions. Temporary shedding may occur within the first few weeks, but new hair growth typically begins after two months and becomes permanent over time. Full results are usually visible within 6 to 12 months. Achieving the desired outcome requires both skilled medical work and patient cooperation throughout the recovery process.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The number of grafts required varies depending on the severity of hair loss. Mild cases may need around 1500–2000 grafts, while more advanced thinning often requires around 3000 grafts or more. In general, a graft contains one to four hair follicles, and the total number of hairs transplanted depends on this composition. For instance, 3000 grafts could result in approximately 9000 individual hairs being implanted, depending on follicle density.</p>
